-- U.S. RESEARCH ROUNDUP-CB&I, Foster Wheeler, Ralph Lauren
-- 
-- Tue Mar 18, 2014 02:35AM EDT
-- None



March 18 (Reuters) - Wall Street securities analysts revised their ratings and price targets on several U.S.-listed companies, including CB&I, Foster Wheeler and Ralph Lauren, on Tuesday.

HIGHLIGHTS * CB&I <CBI.N>: Cowen and Company starts with an outperform rating;  * Foster Wheeler AG <FWLT.O>: Cowen and company starts with market perform rating  * G-III Apparel <GIII.O>, PVH Corp <PVH.N>: Barclays starts with overweight [ID:nWNAB04FEF]   Following is a summary of research actions on U.S. companies reported by Reuters on Tuesday. Stock entries are in alphabetical order.* AbbVie Inc <ABBV.N>: JP Morgan raises price target to $55 from $51; rating neutral * Alliance Fiber Optic Products <AFOP.O>: B.Riley raises to buy from neutral * CB&I <CBI.N>: Cowen and Company starts with an outperform rating; price target $98 * Coach Inc <COH.N>: Barclays starts with equal weight; price target $52  * Derma Sciences <DSCI.O>: Canaccord Genuity cuts target price to $21 from $22; rating buy * Foster Wheeler AG <FWLT.O>: Cowen and company starts with market perform; target $31 * Gap Inc <GPS.N>: Susquehanna cuts price target to $43 from $44; rating neutral * G-III Apparel Group <GIII.O>: Barclays starts with overweight; price target $82 * II-VI Inc <IIVI.O>: D.A. Davidson cuts price target to $17 from $18; rating neutral * II-VI Inc <IIVI.O>: B. Riley cuts price target to $15.75 from $18; rating neutral  * Kate Spade & Co <KATE.N>: Barclays starts with overweight; price target $50   * Michael Kors Holdings <KORS.N>: Barclays starts with underweight; price target $85 * Nordstrom Inc <JWN.N>: Barclays starts with equal weight; price target $65  * Northwest Pipe <NWPX.O>: Jefferies cuts target price to $35 from $39; rating hold * PVH Corp <PVH.N>: Barclays starts with overweight; price target $140  * Ralph Lauren Corp <RL.N>: Barclays starts with overweight; price target $180  * Sterling Construction Co <STRL.O>: D.A. Davidson cuts price target to $10.50 from $11 * Vince Holding Corp <VNCE.N>: Barclays starts with equal weight; price target $28